WEBVTT

00:09.617 --> 00:10.617
Blake: Hey, Val.

00:10.651 --> 00:11.977
Valerie: You smell like dirty diapers.

00:12.097 --> 00:13.295
Blake: Then why don't you change me?

00:13.631 --> 00:14.588
Owen: Whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:14.710 --> 00:16.242
Is this clown bothering you, Val?

00:16.277 --> 00:17.578
Blake: No!

00:17.613 --> 00:20.615
We were just having a...sweet,
flirty back-and-forth.

00:20.649 --> 00:21.982
Owen: What'd you say to me, shrimp?

00:22.017 --> 00:22.717
Blake: Nothing.

00:22.785 --> 00:23.651
Owen: [ Exhales sharply ]

00:23.685 --> 00:26.353
I thought so.

00:26.422 --> 00:27.688
Dori: Mail call.

00:27.723 --> 00:28.890
Letter for Blake.

00:28.924 --> 00:30.324
Blake: [ Sighs ]

00:30.358 --> 00:30.725
What?

00:30.793 --> 00:33.628
The Jews want me to help
them go number two?

00:33.695 --> 00:38.232
Cat: No, it says, "jury
duty," not "jewie-doodie."

00:38.266 --> 00:40.501
Blake: Well, what -- what's jury duty?

00:40.536 --> 00:42.737
Lola: You know what the justice
system is, right, Blake?

00:42.805 --> 00:45.239
Blake: I feel like this
is a trick question.

00:45.273 --> 00:48.509
Um...there <i>is</i> no justice system?

00:48.544 --> 00:50.711
[ Laughter ]

00:50.779 --> 00:51.612
Valerie: I knew it.

00:51.647 --> 00:54.615
Blake: Why are you always
picking on me, huh?

00:54.650 --> 00:55.917
Owen: 'Cause you're a jumbo shrimp.

00:55.951 --> 00:56.451
Oh!

00:56.485 --> 00:57.718
[ Laughter ]

00:57.753 --> 00:58.553
High five.

00:58.620 --> 01:01.288
[ Grunts ]

01:01.323 --> 01:01.923
Lola: Hey, hey.

01:01.957 --> 01:02.723
What's the charge?

01:02.791 --> 01:03.558
I'm an attorney.

01:03.592 --> 01:04.425
Wrongful death.

01:04.459 --> 01:06.260
He slapped a child in
surgery, and he died.

01:06.294 --> 01:08.262
Owen: Let me go, you shrimp.

01:11.667 --> 01:13.434
Glenn: Why did you say
you were a lawyer?

01:13.469 --> 01:14.435
Lola: Because I am one.

01:14.470 --> 01:15.903
Look, I don't have any pets or friends.

01:15.938 --> 01:17.705
I don't watch a lot of
TV, and I'm single.

01:17.739 --> 01:19.740
So I got a law degree and
passed the bar last summer.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.275
Glenn: I will totally buy that.

01:21.309 --> 01:25.279
Lola: Glenn, Cat, if we're gonna
save Owen, I'm gonna need your help.

01:25.313 --> 01:26.013
Cat: We're in.

01:26.047 --> 01:28.916
And if my hunch is right, the
first thing we should do is pay

01:28.984 --> 01:31.385
a little visit to a certain
Childrens Hospital.

01:31.453 --> 01:33.020
Glenn: Let's go.

01:33.088 --> 01:36.824
[ Siren wailing ]

01:38.994 --> 01:40.828
Owen: How are you a doctor and a lawyer?

01:40.896 --> 01:43.397
Lola: Single, no pets, no
friends, no TV, passed the bar.

01:43.431 --> 01:44.765
Owen: I will totally buy that.

01:44.833 --> 01:45.666
Lola: Right.

01:45.701 --> 01:46.667
[ Cellphone rings ]

01:46.735 --> 01:48.302
Oh, okay. Hey, what do you got?

01:48.370 --> 01:50.771
Glenn: So on the day of the
surgery, the kid that Owen

01:50.806 --> 01:52.573
slapped to death took a Lamaze class.

01:52.608 --> 01:52.840
Wait.

01:52.908 --> 01:54.274
But that's for pregnant moms.

01:54.309 --> 01:56.377
Why would --
Lola: Hey, I don't deal in "why woulds."

01:56.411 --> 01:59.580
I deal in "you shoulds," as in you <i>shoulds</i>
go talk to that Lamaze teacher.

01:59.648 --> 02:01.482
Glenn: We wills.

02:01.550 --> 02:05.586
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:05.621 --> 02:07.354
Owen: Oh, no.

02:07.389 --> 02:09.490
Look in the jury box.

02:09.525 --> 02:10.758
Blake: Well, well, well.

02:10.826 --> 02:11.692
Dr. Owen maestro.

02:11.760 --> 02:15.596
How the tables have turned, my friend.

02:15.664 --> 02:17.464
Wait. Do you know him?

02:17.499 --> 02:21.502
'Cause that would disqualify
you from serving on this jury.

02:21.570 --> 02:22.970
Blake: [ Smacks lips ]

02:23.038 --> 02:23.971
No, I do not.

02:24.006 --> 02:28.108
That's...just the way
I talk, my friend.

02:28.143 --> 02:28.943
[ Crinkling ]

02:28.977 --> 02:31.946
Are you wearing a diaper?

02:31.980 --> 02:33.414
Lola: I'm gonna be honest.

02:33.481 --> 02:34.381
I am very nervous.

02:34.416 --> 02:35.416
Owen: Oh, it's okay.

02:35.483 --> 02:35.950
Just relax.

02:35.984 --> 02:38.019
Lola: And when I'm
nervous, I do cocaine.

02:38.053 --> 02:39.053
Owen: What? Shut up.

02:39.120 --> 02:40.320
All rise.

02:40.388 --> 02:43.691
The honorable judge Lester
Harrison presiding.

02:43.759 --> 02:45.526
Lola: Oh, do not let
me say the "N" word.

02:45.561 --> 02:45.960
Owen: What?

02:46.028 --> 02:46.894
Why would you say that?

02:46.962 --> 02:47.962
Lola: Cocaine.

02:48.030 --> 02:50.431
Judge Harrison: You may be seated.

02:50.465 --> 02:52.533
Opening remarks, Ms. Spratt?

02:52.601 --> 02:56.537
Lola: [ Sighs ] Okay.

02:56.605 --> 03:03.077
N-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n-n...
Ni-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i... ckel.

03:03.144 --> 03:04.612
Nickel!

03:04.646 --> 03:09.617
If I...had a nickel for every
time a responsible doctor was

03:09.651 --> 03:13.955
falsely accused, well, I
would be one rich [Bleep]

03:13.989 --> 03:14.722
Objection.

03:14.790 --> 03:17.458
Judge Harrison: I'll allow it,
but you'd better be going

03:17.525 --> 03:18.859
somewhere with this, counselor.

03:18.894 --> 03:19.994
Lola: Mm-hmm.

03:20.062 --> 03:22.362
Sure, that boy has been
in here a few times.

03:22.430 --> 03:23.631
He's gonna make a great mom.

03:23.665 --> 03:24.431
Glenn: Hmm.

03:24.466 --> 03:25.633
Anything unusual about him?

03:25.667 --> 03:26.500
Uh, yes.

03:26.534 --> 03:29.904
Most of my students are pregnant
women, and he was neither.

03:29.938 --> 03:31.005
Cat: Anything else?

03:31.039 --> 03:33.641
Did he ever mention any plans
to die during surgery?

03:33.709 --> 03:34.008
No.

03:34.076 --> 03:37.177
We just did some deep-breathing
exercises together.

03:37.212 --> 03:40.982
You see, Lamaze was originally
invented as just a humorous fad,

03:41.016 --> 03:43.550
but it turns out it can relax anyone.

03:43.619 --> 03:45.552
Cat: Class that teaches
you to breathe, huh?

03:45.587 --> 03:47.454
Glenn: What will they
teach next -- swimming?

03:47.522 --> 03:49.924
You know what, if you really
want to get some information,

03:49.958 --> 03:51.425
you should talk to Sy Mittleman.

03:51.459 --> 03:53.094
He is the biggest gossip at Childrens.

03:53.161 --> 03:56.463
Glenn: Yeah, and where can
we find this "Sy Mittleman"?

03:56.531 --> 03:58.833
Keep going straight past, "have
you heard?" And then take

03:58.900 --> 04:00.901
a quick right at, "oh, no she didn't."

04:00.936 --> 04:01.936
[ Chuckles ] Front blobby.

04:02.004 --> 04:02.837
Glenn: Blobby?

04:02.871 --> 04:04.571
Take off the "B" and you'll know.

04:04.640 --> 04:05.640
Glenn: Lobby. Got it.

04:05.707 --> 04:07.474
Cat: Let's go.

04:07.509 --> 04:09.209
I hope Lola's okay.

04:09.244 --> 04:10.811
Lola: [ Inhales deeply ]

04:10.846 --> 04:11.746
Oh, God. Whoo!

04:11.780 --> 04:12.479
[ Sniffs ]

04:12.547 --> 04:16.017
[ Muttering, laughing ]

04:16.051 --> 04:16.916
Okay.

04:16.985 --> 04:19.185
Owen: You have <i>got</i> to
stop doing cocaine.

04:19.220 --> 04:20.821
Lola: [ Breathlessly ] Okay.

04:20.856 --> 04:24.992
Your honor, I would like to call an expert
medical witness to the stand -- myself.

04:25.027 --> 04:27.662
Objection -- on the grounds
that I'm like, "What?"

04:27.729 --> 04:28.462
[ Chuckles ]

04:28.496 --> 04:31.498
Judge Harrison: I'll allow it,
but you'd better be going

04:31.566 --> 04:33.100
somewhere with this, counselor.

04:33.135 --> 04:37.038
Lola: Josh graven was suffering from
benign epidermal non-carcinoma.

04:37.105 --> 04:38.039
It's a big mole.

04:38.106 --> 04:42.677
The chances of surviving
that operation -- 0.001%.

04:42.711 --> 04:44.045
Owen didn't kill that kid.

04:44.112 --> 04:45.680
A bully named <i>chances</i> did.

04:45.714 --> 04:46.213
[ Sighs ]

04:46.281 --> 04:47.648
No further questions.

04:47.683 --> 04:50.217
[ Grunts ]

04:50.285 --> 04:53.220
Dr. Spratt, you <i>may</i> be an
expert in the medical field.

04:53.254 --> 04:54.021
Lola: Yep.

04:54.056 --> 04:57.692
But you are a novice in the
area of putting transparencies

04:57.726 --> 05:00.695
on overhead projectors.

05:00.762 --> 05:02.029
Lola: [ Gasps ]

05:02.064 --> 05:05.132
No. [ Breathing heavily ]

05:05.167 --> 05:06.834
Blake: [ Whispering ] Hey.

05:06.868 --> 05:09.203
Great move, bro.

05:09.237 --> 05:11.138
Wait. Is he your brother?

05:11.206 --> 05:12.707
Blake: No.

05:12.741 --> 05:15.509
It's just the way I talk...bro.

05:17.245 --> 05:18.779
Sy: Ha. You little minx.

05:18.814 --> 05:20.781
Cat: Mr. Mittleman, can we have a word?

05:20.849 --> 05:22.049
Sy: Got to go, girlfriend.

05:22.084 --> 05:22.950
You hear the news?

05:22.984 --> 05:25.586
Lamaze teacher told you to
come down here and talk to me.

05:25.620 --> 05:28.055
Cat: I guess you really <i>are the
eyes and ears of this hospital.</i>

05:28.090 --> 05:30.257
<i>Glenn: What do you know about
Josh graven, the boy who died</i>

05:30.325 --> 05:33.127
<i>during Owen's surgery?</i>

05:35.330 --> 05:38.665
<i>Sy: Listen, I heard that he was
faking his illness in order</i>

05:38.700 --> 05:40.067
<i>to get some plastic surgery.</i>

05:40.102 --> 05:41.035
<i>Sound familiar, Glenn?</i>

05:41.069 --> 05:42.669
<i>Glenn: I had a deviated septum.</i>

05:42.704 --> 05:44.238
<i>Sy: Want to hear the real skinny?</i>

05:44.272 --> 05:47.041
<i>You go down the morgue and you
check on that little kid's body.</i>

05:47.075 --> 05:49.877
<i>Talking about bodies, guess who
put on a few pounds after their</i>

05:49.911 --> 05:50.978
<i>well-publicized nuptials?</i>

05:51.012 --> 05:52.947
<i>Glenn: Shot in the
dark -- Tilda Swinton?</i>

05:52.981 --> 05:53.714
<i>Sy: No.</i>

05:53.749 --> 05:54.715
<i>Cat: Let's go.</i>

05:54.750 --> 05:55.883
<i>Sy: One more thing.</i>

05:55.951 --> 05:59.253
<i>Dr. Valerie flame is going to be
called as a surprise witness for</i>

05:59.287 --> 06:01.055
<i>the prosecution.</i>

06:01.089 --> 06:01.789
<i>Cat: Uh-oh.</i>

06:01.823 --> 06:03.057
<i>I'm gonna go to the courtroom.</i>

06:03.091 --> 06:05.092
<i>You go to the morgue.</i>

06:05.127 --> 06:06.160
<i>[ Cellphone rings ]</i>

06:06.228 --> 06:07.061
<i>Sy: Hello.</i>

06:07.095 --> 06:08.262
<i>Want to hear the news?</i>

06:08.296 --> 06:09.529
<i>You just called me.</i>

06:09.597 --> 06:13.734
<i>And in the time you've known Dr. Maestro,
have you ever known</i>

06:13.769 --> 06:15.736
<i>him to be...rough with people?</i>

06:15.804 --> 06:18.005
<i>Valerie: He had a bank of
school lockers installed at the</i>

06:18.073 --> 06:21.008
<i>hospital so that he'd have
something to "push nerds into."</i>

06:21.076 --> 06:22.143
<i>Blake: Hmm.</i>

06:22.177 --> 06:24.912
<i>Personally, I'd be like, "guilty!"</i>

06:24.980 --> 06:29.183
<i>But out of respect for the court
procedure, I'm all, "let's wait</i>

06:29.251 --> 06:30.284
<i>till the end."</i>

06:30.351 --> 06:30.918
<i>Lola: Oh!</i>

06:30.986 --> 06:31.786
<i>A moment, your honor.</i>

06:31.820 --> 06:33.788
<i>Judge Harrison: I'll allow it...
Lola: Great.</i>

06:33.822 --> 06:35.923
<i>Judge Harrison: ...But you'd
better be going somewhere with</i>

06:35.991 --> 06:36.657
<i>this, counselor.</i>

06:36.724 --> 06:37.792
<i>Lola: Thank you, your honor.</i>

06:37.826 --> 06:39.626
<i>Judge Harrison: What,
I'm not gonna allow it?</i>

06:39.661 --> 06:41.262
<i>I'm not</i> gonna see where this is going?

06:41.296 --> 06:43.097
Cat: Here's the coke you asked for.

06:43.165 --> 06:44.098
Lola: Thank God.

06:44.132 --> 06:44.932
Two secs, judge?

06:44.966 --> 06:45.365
Two secs.

06:45.400 --> 06:46.834
[ Sniffs ] Ha!

06:46.868 --> 06:47.301
[ Snorts ]

06:47.368 --> 06:49.170
Is Dr. Owen maestro a good person?

06:49.204 --> 06:49.636
No.

06:49.704 --> 06:52.206
In fact, what this witness
forgot to mention is that he

06:52.240 --> 06:54.574
gave two-thirds of the
hospital staff crabs.

06:54.642 --> 06:56.844
Isn't that right, Dr. Valerie flame?

06:56.912 --> 06:57.744
Valerie: Yes.

06:57.779 --> 07:02.716
Lola: Did he give <i>you</i> crabs, Dr. flame?

07:02.750 --> 07:03.383
Valerie: Yes.

07:03.418 --> 07:04.118
Lola: Yes.

07:04.186 --> 07:05.085
[ Spectators groan ]

07:05.120 --> 07:07.087
This witness is biased.

07:07.122 --> 07:07.721
Boom!

07:07.755 --> 07:09.023
No further questions.

07:09.090 --> 07:10.925
♪ No further questions ♪

07:10.992 --> 07:12.827
♪ no further questions ♪

07:12.861 --> 07:13.861
[ Normal voice ] Unh.

07:13.929 --> 07:14.728
[ Laughs ]

07:14.762 --> 07:16.197
Owen: That was amazing.

07:16.264 --> 07:18.032
Lola: What just happened?

07:18.066 --> 07:19.934
I am high right now.

07:20.001 --> 07:21.135
[ Laughs ]

07:21.169 --> 07:22.769
[ Sniffs ] Ah!

07:22.838 --> 07:24.839
Oh. [ Grunts ]

07:24.873 --> 07:26.040
I got this.

07:26.074 --> 07:27.107
[ Exhales sharply ]

07:27.142 --> 07:32.112
Ladies and gentlemen of the
jury, I know what bullying is.

07:32.147 --> 07:35.382
I am both a doctor <i>and</i> a lawyer
because of overbearing parents

07:35.416 --> 07:36.851
who pushed me too hard.

07:36.918 --> 07:39.119
Also I'm single and no pets, et cetera.

07:39.154 --> 07:44.325
In a sense, I was bullied
into becoming a huge success.

07:44.392 --> 07:48.762
Bullying can <i>good.</i>

07:48.796 --> 07:51.232
<i>Yes, sometimes it has
consequences, like a kid is</i>

07:51.299 --> 07:55.336
<i>slapped to death or you develop
a massive cocaine habit.</i>

07:55.403 --> 07:58.873
<i>Dr. maestro slapped a
kid, and that kid died.</i>

07:58.907 --> 08:02.409
<i>But to hold him responsible
would be like blaming</i>

08:02.477 --> 08:07.781
<i>John Lennon's death on
Mark David Chapman.</i>

08:07.815 --> 08:11.252
<i>Now, as a lawyer, I
search for the truth.</i>

08:11.319 --> 08:16.223
<i>But as a doctor, I can tell you
it swims in and out of that</i>

08:16.258 --> 08:23.697
<i>magical muscle that you
laypeople call..."The heart."</i>

08:23.731 --> 08:25.699
<i>The defense rests.</i>

08:25.733 --> 08:28.869
<i>Dr. Maestro slapped that
kid so he'd fight to live.</i>

08:28.904 --> 08:31.972
<i>All in favor of innocent?</i>

08:32.006 --> 08:34.875
<i>Blake: [ Chuckles ]</i>

08:34.943 --> 08:37.811
<i>Sounds like you're all too
afraid to convict a bully like</i>

08:37.879 --> 08:40.147
<i>Owen Maestro.</i>

08:40.181 --> 08:41.148
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

08:41.182 --> 08:43.150
<i>Look at yourselves. No?</i>

08:43.183 --> 08:43.984
<i>Okay, I will.</i>

08:44.019 --> 08:46.353
<i>You -- you're like, "Uh,
I'm writing with my pen."</i>

08:46.388 --> 08:49.356
<i>You're like, "I got a pen, too,
but I'm not even as good as that</i>

08:49.424 --> 08:49.890
<i>guy."</i>

08:49.958 --> 08:53.360
<i>And you're like... [ babbling ]</i>

08:53.395 --> 08:54.061
<i>Stop it.</i>

08:54.095 --> 08:58.899
<i>Why are you picking on us?</i>

08:58.967 --> 09:00.334
<i>Blake: Oh, my God.</i>

09:00.368 --> 09:01.235
<i>He's right.</i>

09:01.269 --> 09:04.171
<i>I've become the very
thing that I condemn.</i>

09:04.205 --> 09:05.806
<i>I'm a bully.</i>

09:05.873 --> 09:10.277
<i>And...I'm...
♪ loving it ♪</i>

09:10.312 --> 09:11.178
<i>All right!</i>

09:11.246 --> 09:15.015
<i>Let's go over this one more
time, shrimp dumplings.</i>

09:15.050 --> 09:18.819
<i>Yeah, you heard me -- shrimp dumplings!</i>

09:18.853 --> 09:20.988
<i>Get used to it.</i>

09:21.022 --> 09:26.093
<i>We, the jury, find Dr. Owen Maestro...
guilty.</i>

09:26.161 --> 09:27.894
<i>[ Spectators murmur ]</i>

09:27.929 --> 09:33.000
<i>I'm like, "Tell me
something I don't </i> know."

09:33.068 --> 09:34.101
Lola: [ Breathing heavily ]

09:34.169 --> 09:35.202
Glenn: [ Squeaking ]

09:35.236 --> 09:36.203
Lola: Oh! Your honor.

09:36.237 --> 09:37.938
I have one more witness
I'd like to call.

09:38.006 --> 09:38.472
Objection.

09:38.506 --> 09:39.739
Judge Harrison: Overruled.

09:39.807 --> 09:40.207
Lola: Yes.

09:40.275 --> 09:43.110
Judge Harrison: I feel I have to allow
it, given my pattern with that.

09:43.178 --> 09:44.011
Lola: Okay.

09:44.079 --> 09:49.850
The defense would like to call to the stand...
Slap-murder victim Josh graven.

09:49.917 --> 09:53.387
[ Spectators murmuring ]

09:53.421 --> 10:00.394
Young man...are you now or
have you ever been...dead?

10:04.866 --> 10:06.133
Blake: Yes.

10:06.167 --> 10:06.800
Yes.

10:06.834 --> 10:08.102
Josh: No.

10:08.136 --> 10:10.471
[ Cheers and applause ]

10:10.505 --> 10:11.938
Judge Harrison: [ Bangs gavel ]

10:12.007 --> 10:12.772
Order in this court!

10:12.840 --> 10:16.843
Lola: [ Laughing ]

10:16.878 --> 10:19.213
Glenn: Found the kid hiding
out in a drawer at the morgue

10:19.280 --> 10:21.281
playing video games and
eating to-mah-to chips.

10:21.316 --> 10:23.050
Lola: But how did he fake his death?

10:23.084 --> 10:24.584
Glenn: Get this -- Lamaze.

10:24.619 --> 10:25.852
Lola: But why?

10:25.887 --> 10:27.321
Cat: Overbearing parents.

10:27.389 --> 10:29.556
Lola: Oh, I have the same problem.

10:29.590 --> 10:32.459
But I'd take a slow death
over a fake one any day.

10:32.494 --> 10:33.927
Blake: Hey, guys.

10:33.961 --> 10:36.330
I, for one, learned a very
valuable lesson today.

10:36.398 --> 10:37.964
Cat: He smells like dirty diapers.

10:37.999 --> 10:39.599
Glenn: He smells exactly
like child feces.

10:39.634 --> 10:42.136
Lola: Yeah, he totally does.

10:42.170 --> 10:44.138
Judge Harrison: I'll allow it.

10:44.172 --> 10:51.512
'Cause I, for one, really want to see
where this is going, "clownselor."

10:51.513 --> 10:53.480
Sal: <i>Attention, courtroom staff.</i>

10:53.515 --> 10:57.317
<i>I've been moonlighting as a P.A.
announcer in the hospital.</i>

10:57.385 --> 10:59.319
<i>That is all.</i>

